bellbird
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an indigenous honey-eating songbird,  Anthornis melanura , also known as korimako, mockymock and mockie.  The bellbird is not, however, a mockingbird like the tui.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka bell-bird, bell bird; mako, makomako, korimako, mock-a-mock, mocker, mockie, korimoko, =mokomoko
